title: Street Cop Training Invoices (Orange County Sheriff's Office)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Any records documenting or summarizing expenditures related to the vendor Street Cop Training, a company that hosts conferences for law enforcement officers, between January 1, 2020 and Dec. 1, 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

CJ Ciaramella

communications.subject: Tennessee Public Records Act Request: Pursuit Footage From 03/31/24
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Dash cam and body cam footage from the pursuit that occurred in the late hours of 03/31/24 into 04/1/24 on i24 in Marion and Grundy counties

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Brian Hicks.

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: True The Vote
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

In November 2022 the USPS told WIRED in a statement (https://www.wired.com/story/true-the-vote-iv3-app-voter-fraud/) True the Vote's alleged use of NCOALink services is under review for violating Terms of Service. I am looking for documents produced as a result of that review. These documents could include emails, memos,  or other records pertaining to the review of True The Votes use of NCOALink. Please also include any emails between representatives of True The Vote and the USPS any invoices paid to the USPS by True the Vote.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Dhruv Mehrotra
